 
    relay_emote()      Eastern Stories II (19 Oct 1995)     relay_emote()
 
    NAME
        relay_emote - interface for emote
 
    SYNOPSIS
        void relay_emote(object me, string verb);
 
    DESCRIPTION
        relay_emote, if present in the target object, will be called
	and the emote verb used against this object will be passed 
	along with the acting object.

        This is used as an interface to handle any interaction triggered
        by the system emote daemon.
 
    SEE ALSO
        relay_say(), relay_channel(), relay_whisper()
 
